39:31.849 --> 39:32.750
Come on, let's talk some hope.

39:32.770 --> 39:46.503
Because I genuinely believe that the things that the internet offers that are good, that can be helpful, but can lean to harmful, are the very things that God has called us as families and communities to offer young people.

39:46.663 --> 39:46.904
Right.

39:47.164 --> 39:51.929
So young people are trying to answer free questions, free big questions.

39:51.989 --> 39:53.490
Every teenager wants to know.

39:54.210 --> 39:55.633
Number one, who am I?

39:55.734 --> 39:57.137
That's the question of identity.

39:58.981 --> 40:00.946
Number two, what am I here for?

40:01.207 --> 40:02.449
That's the question of purpose.

40:03.291 --> 40:06.098
Number three, where do I fit?

40:06.178 --> 40:07.580
That's the question of belonging.

40:07.981 --> 40:15.974
Identity, purpose and belonging is the question of every generation of our advocate and doesn't the gospel and the church answer that beautifully.

40:16.234 --> 40:17.256
That is the question.

40:17.276 --> 40:20.942
It isn't the place where belonging can truly exist.

40:21.443 --> 40:24.808
We have abdicated parenting responsibility to Alexa.

40:25.229 --> 40:27.292
Alexa now tells us bedtime stories.

40:28.073 --> 40:28.434
Yeah.

40:28.962 --> 40:32.787
and make silly noises and tells us dad jokes, that's for the dad.

40:34.670 --> 40:50.852
And I genuinely believe that we as the church have this hope that's found in Christ and this hope that's found in community where we have young people and when we talk about AI, we've got young relationships that are being outsourced to a mobile phone.

40:52.134 --> 40:58.002
And we are now moving in today's when young people are falling in love with their chatbot

40:59.106 --> 41:06.281
And again, it sounds ridiculous to say, but it's real, and we're heading towards days, and we're already there when the robots come.

41:07.503 --> 41:11.551
And they'll be walking amongst us, and I sound ridiculous saying it, but it is coming.

41:12.173 --> 41:16.401
It's when we're now disembodying technology and removing the humanity.

41:16.441 --> 41:18.425
So what do we as the church do to respond?

41:19.007 --> 41:20.690
We move forward.

41:20.994 --> 41:24.017
in unity with authentic humanity.

41:24.278 --> 41:28.623
And we restore the ground of children being able to be children again.

41:29.063 --> 41:33.328
We retake the ground of what it means to have genuine authentic relationships.

41:33.568 --> 41:34.950
We forget digital campfires.

41:34.970 --> 41:36.772
We get young people around campfires.

41:37.052 --> 41:38.975
We get young people around tables again.

41:39.255 --> 41:45.362
We get young people connected to multi-generations, learning things they will never learn from chat GPT.

41:45.410 --> 41:59.986
The church is, you and I are called to be the embodied community, the hands and feet of Jesus to the world and to answer those questions because if we don't answer these questions of a density purpose and belonging for children, somebody else will.

42:00.446 --> 42:05.972
And right now our children are being discipled by data and they've been discipled by an algorithm.

42:05.992 --> 42:07.273
That is what discipleship means.

42:07.333 --> 42:11.698
It literally means formation of spirituality and humanity.

42:11.842 --> 42:22.065
We have abdicated responsibility and we've said that Mark Zuckerberg and Elon Musk and these guys can disciple our children when we are the ones who are responsible for it.

42:22.325 --> 42:24.710
That is the God-given mandate for you and me, right?

42:27.176 --> 42:27.978
Yes, Dave.

42:28.078 --> 42:31.826
I mean, I hear your passion and I mirror it because

42:32.162 --> 42:34.845
That should be our USP as chair.

42:34.865 --> 42:36.586
That's the USP, not the USP.

42:36.606 --> 42:39.889
Identity belonging purpose, that's what we exist for.

42:40.330 --> 42:46.636
And church, you know, when we talk about stepping into the story, so often what we think about is ourselves.

42:46.976 --> 42:49.098
We think about our own fulfillment.

42:49.438 --> 42:57.466
But actually, there is a generation that needs us to be thinking about them and their fulfillment and their flourishing and their thriving.

42:57.846 --> 43:01.810
I'm tired of asking for volunteers for kids' church.

43:02.018 --> 43:11.854
Do you know what, why do we see that as a lesser ministry, our kids and our youth, when actually these are the ones who will be carrying the baton of faith forward, they already are.

43:12.214 --> 43:14.839
They're representing Jesus, day in, day out.

43:15.259 --> 43:19.506
Come on church, if this doesn't compel you to make a difference, I don't know what would.

43:20.788 --> 43:21.189
That's it.

43:22.090 --> 43:26.898
And there's so much hope, isn't there, in that, as we can offer things

43:27.522 --> 43:29.204
that chatbots never can.

43:30.206 --> 43:36.434
You know, your data does not really know you and your data does not want the best for you.

43:36.975 --> 43:41.581
They want to hold your attention and they want to monetize that attention.

43:41.701 --> 43:43.204
It's simple as that.

43:43.224 --> 43:45.066
That is the purpose of all of this stuff.

43:46.067 --> 43:49.312
If the product is free, you are the product.

43:51.275 --> 43:53.778
And that's why we as adults have to remember that

43:53.890 --> 43:57.213
I'm really challenged by all this stuff, because I've got to get a hold of this for myself.

43:57.294 --> 43:59.436
So I feel challenged to be.

43:59.496 --> 44:06.743
My wife came off social media about eight months ago, and she's had no fear of missing out, and she's better for her.

44:07.184 --> 44:10.567
And I know we can be tech-negative, or we can be tech-positive.

44:10.587 --> 44:12.429
I believe we need to be tech-wise in all of this.

44:12.589 --> 44:13.090
That's great.

44:13.530 --> 44:20.818
And I regularly take Instagram off my phone, and at the weekend, put it back on, and then my daughter just teases me, because she's like, you've got it back on again, have you, Dad?

44:21.826 --> 44:23.288
Thanks, love.

44:23.308 --> 44:31.859
So we've got to model something in our churches and model something in our communities and model something in our families that's different for the next generation.

44:32.359 --> 44:36.244
And one of the big challenges is that we don't even know and understand it ourselves.

44:36.405 --> 44:36.525
Right.

44:36.825 --> 44:38.708
I mean, I really struggle to switch off from that.

44:38.828 --> 44:43.794
I love communicating with people, which is a beautiful strength, but it's also a

44:43.906 --> 44:51.056
There's a terrible underside to that, which is, you know, when you have a tool at your disposal that keeps you connected, how do you withdraw from that?

44:51.076 --> 44:55.762
And it's something I'm learning, but I definitely don't have a handle on it all the time.

44:55.782 --> 44:57.424
So, I'm with you.

44:57.664 --> 44:58.466
Can I give you a hint?

44:58.566 --> 44:59.106
Yes, please.

44:59.527 --> 45:10.802
I went for a walk with my daughter, dear Adi, she's Janelle for 15, and I actually was honest with her about my tech use and phone use, and we had a long conversations with walking along about changes that we wanted to make.

45:10.946 --> 45:13.329
And I think one of the best things we can do is do it together.

45:13.589 --> 45:14.310
That's great.

45:14.470 --> 45:15.131
I love that.

45:15.331 --> 45:15.931
Genuinely.

45:16.031 --> 45:23.720
And we're both making changes and we're challenged and she actually needed to hear because we all know that they spot our hypocrisy at Marloff, right?

45:24.120 --> 45:24.380
Right.

45:25.502 --> 45:27.204
100% unconstantly called out.

45:27.584 --> 45:30.027
It's kind of do as I say, not as I do.

45:30.427 --> 45:33.971
And that doesn't work in a generation of leading influencers.

45:34.712 --> 45:34.952
Right.

45:35.613 --> 45:38.516
Oh, we're already over time, Dave.

45:38.536 --> 45:40.658
So I'm just trying to think about

45:40.770 --> 45:45.637
AI, because I feel like that's so useful, but I'm also really mindful of our kids' church team.

45:47.360 --> 45:48.342
Pete's going to go up and chat.

45:48.442 --> 45:56.795
Let's just do this last question as fast as we can on AI, but I don't want people to miss out on that, because I feel like probably that's something that we really, really need to learn about.

45:57.376 --> 45:58.998
So the question is this.

45:59.459 --> 46:09.394
The final feature is this is a generation who are AI-shaped, and how can we help raise a generation who are wise

46:09.538 --> 46:18.868
and discerning and provide them with authenticity, truth, and real human interaction in an increasingly artificial world.

46:19.128 --> 46:22.452
Yeah, we've touched on it already, and it's such a massive question.

46:23.053 --> 46:28.599
So I think one of the biggest things that we can do is to learn about AI and what's happening, the reality of the world.

46:28.639 --> 46:31.322
And again, there's some incredible positive things happening.

46:32.022 --> 46:35.346
But the world is changing at such a pace right now.

46:35.586 --> 46:39.450
that in two or three years time we're in danger of looking back and going what happened.

46:41.112 --> 46:43.515
So I think as Christians we've got to be ahead of the game with it.

46:44.076 --> 46:52.044
We need to understand that our children have been now given tools to be able to say something and create worlds.

46:52.064 --> 46:54.307
They've been given godlike powers in childlike minds.

46:54.868 --> 47:00.594
So you can now do text to image, you can do text to story, you can do voice to video game,

47:01.282 --> 47:02.223
voice to video.

47:02.243 --> 47:13.960
So if I say make me a world where Pete is on his guitar running around popping balloons and it'll do it and I'll send you it later Pete and I can interact and I can play that.

47:14.601 --> 47:29.202
So young people have been given incredible amount of power in the palm of their hands so we've got to help them learn to discern and it's not just if they can do it, it should they be and then I believe ethics is going to be at the heart of this

47:29.314 --> 47:35.180
talk and the morality of it in the next generation, because we're going to have the tools and it's coming and it's happening.

47:35.620 --> 47:53.257
So I would say in one short thing, and then I want to talk about Jesus to end if that's okay, is that get to know what's going on in the world of AI and help have a conversation with your children, young people again about how it's impacting them, because it is affecting absolutely everything.

47:54.939 --> 47:57.141
And if I was to land it on Jesus, I would say this.

47:57.601 --> 47:58.162
Come on.

47:58.594 --> 48:00.898
Jesus is good news for Generation Alpha.

48:02.160 --> 48:05.065
For the anxious-minded Jesus is the Prince of Peace.

48:06.367 --> 48:12.937
For the leading influencer, Jesus is our servant king, the one who wants to lead us into his amazing kingdom.

48:13.739 --> 48:19.388
For the pandemic impacted Jesus is Emmanuel, God with us in all of our problems and trials.

48:20.349 --> 48:25.618
For the hyper-connected Jesus is the true vine, our real genuine source of connection.

48:26.690 --> 48:31.457
And from the AI shapes, Jesus is our wisdom and He's our truth.

48:34.542 --> 48:35.723
Yes to that.

48:36.825 --> 48:40.791
Jesus is good news for every generation and He's really good news for Gen Alpha.

48:41.572 --> 48:42.714
I really do believe that.

48:42.774 --> 48:44.777
Can we just say it firstly, thank you, Dave?

48:45.138 --> 48:45.578
Thanks, guys.

48:45.738 --> 48:50.966
For condensing a labour of love into 35 minutes for us.

48:52.669 --> 48:53.490
Secondly,

48:53.570 --> 48:56.495
I would love us to think about how we can get hold of this book.

48:56.635 --> 49:11.058
I would encourage everyone in our church family to read this book and I'm not saying that because I want Dave to have loads of book sales, although I do actually because it's not easy to be a creative and it's like putting your baby out there and you want everybody to read it, don't you?

49:11.266 --> 49:24.219
Every three chairs or so, there is a postcard here, and on that postcard, there is a QR code you can sign up to pre-order Dave's book, or yes, you can zoom in right now to the screen behind me and do it that way.

49:24.259 --> 49:24.639
Yeah.

49:25.540 --> 49:31.205
And I think if you want to, if you get chance, if the easiest way, go on Amazon, type in raise in gen alpha.

49:31.846 --> 49:34.929
If you pre-order it, it makes a huge difference.

49:34.949 --> 49:38.873
If it gets on Amazon's radar, that then means they push it out more as well.

49:38.893 --> 49:39.754
So that'd be fantastic.

49:39.794 --> 49:40.274
Thank you.

49:40.898 --> 49:41.379
Thank you.

49:41.819 --> 49:42.460
Yay.

49:42.901 --> 49:47.307
And for those everyone who's ordered, if you do, I will give you a personal high five this morning.

49:48.268 --> 49:49.049
Oh, well, there you go.

49:49.069 --> 49:50.891
If that's not an incentive, I don't know what it is.

49:50.951 --> 49:52.273
Could we stand together, Church?

49:56.339 --> 49:58.141
I want to finish with a quote from Dave.

49:59.983 --> 50:07.954
Jen Alpha is the most spiritually curious generation yet, but they need a place to call home.

50:12.002 --> 50:18.631
Listen Church, we want to become that place called home for Gen Alpha, don't we?

50:19.673 --> 50:27.644
We want to be ready and that's going to take all of us growing, changing and making space, myself included.

50:31.108 --> 50:32.490
I wonder, oh, he's gone.

50:33.271 --> 50:38.098
Dave, would you just come and pray for us to become that place called home for Gen Alpha, please?

50:38.498 --> 50:44.304
And then we're going to sing the song that Dave alluded to, Hosanna, about a generation rising up to take their place.

50:44.384 --> 50:47.827
And for some of us, maybe God will break our hearts this morning.

50:48.348 --> 50:49.869
We'll have our ministry team here.

50:49.929 --> 50:57.437
If you'd like to stand with someone in prayer to take your place in discipling Jen Alpha, we would love you to do that.

51:00.300 --> 51:06.546
Holy Spirit, we lift every Jen Alpha in this room and in our lives, in our hearts, you right now.

51:07.618 --> 51:15.830
Holy Spirit, we ask that you would equip them with the tools to be disciples of Jesus in their generation.

51:17.693 --> 51:21.939
Lord, you say in a word that David served the purposes of God in his generation.

51:21.979 --> 51:26.886
Now let it be for Janal, for that they would serve the purposes of God to their generation.

51:27.947 --> 51:35.218
We pray protection, we pray the empowering of those that need to know that Jesus is good news right now.

51:35.810 --> 51:42.480
I pray you would raise them up to be influencers, to be leaders in the nation and in the nations of the world.

51:43.561 --> 51:47.186
And above all, Lord, we thank you, God, that you are the God of generations.

51:48.428 --> 52:00.265
And in line with Ephesians, we pray, Lord, that you are able to do exceedingly more than we could ever hope, dare, or dream, or imagine for the sake of the next generation.

52:00.325 --> 52:02.368
We pray this in Jesus' name.

52:03.089 --> 52:03.570
Amen.

